INSERT INTO `FLAWS` (`FLAW_ID`, `FLAW_DESC`, `BOOK`, `PAGE`) VALUES
(1, 'I judge others harshly, and myself even more severely.', 'Online', 0),
(2, 'I put too much trust in those who wield power within my temple\'s hierarchy.', 'Online', 0),
(3, 'My piety sometimes leads me to blindly trust those that profess faith in my god.', 'Online', 0),
(4, 'I am inflexible in my thinking.', 'Online', 0),
(5, 'I am suspicious of strangers and suspect the worst of them.', 'Online', 0),
(6, 'Once I pick a goal, I become obsessed with it to the detriment of everything else in my life.', 'Online', 0),
(7, 'I can\'t resist a pretty face.', 'Online', 0),
(8, 'I\'m always in debt. I spend my illgotten gains on decadent luxuries faster than I bring them in.', 'Online', 0),
(9, 'I\'m convinced that no one could ever fool me in the way I fool others.', 'Online', 0),
(10, 'I\'m too greedy for my own good. I can\'t resist taking a risk if there\'s money involved.', 'Online', 0),
(11, 'I can\'t resist swindling people who are more powerful than me.', 'Online', 0),
(12, 'I hate to admit it and will hate myself for it, but I\'ll run and preserve my own hide if the going gets tough.', 'Online', 0),
(13, 'When I see something valuable, I can\'t think about Athing but how to steal it.', 'Online', 0),
(14, 'When faced with a choice between money and my friends, I usually choose the money.', 'Online', 0),
(15, 'If there\'s a plan, I\'ll forget it. If I don\'t forget it, I\'ll ignore it.', 'Online', 0),
(16, 'I have a \'tell\' that reveals when I\'m lying.', 'Online', 0),
(17, 'I turn tail and run when things go bad.', 'Online', 0),
(18, 'An innocent person is in prison for a crime that I committed. I\'m okay with that.', 'Online', 0),
(19, 'I\'ll do Athing to win fame and renown.', 'Online', 0),
(20, 'I\'m a sucker for a pretty face.', 'Online', 0),
(21, 'A scandal prevents me from ever going home again. That kind of trouble seems to follow me around.', 'Online', 0),
(22, 'I once satirized a noble who still wants my head. It was a mistake that I will likely repeat.', 'Online', 0),
(23, 'I have trouble keeping my true feelings hidden. My sharp tongue lands me in trouble.', 'Online', 0),
(24, 'Despite my best efforts, I am unreliable to my friends.', 'Online', 0),
(25, 'The tyrant who rules my land will stop at nothing to see me killed.', 'Online', 0),
(26, 'I\'m convinced of the significance of my destiny, and blind to my shortcomings and the risk of failure.', 'Online', 0),
(27, 'The people who knew me when I was young know my shameful secret, so I can never go home again.', 'Online', 0),
(28, 'I have a weakness for the vices of the city, especially hard drink.', 'Online', 0),
(29, 'Secretly, I believe that things would be better if I were a tyrant lording over the land.', 'Online', 0),
(30, 'I have trouble trusting in my allies.', 'Online', 0),
(31, 'I\'ll do Athing to get my hands on something rare or priceless.', 'Online', 0),
(32, 'I\'m quick to assume that someone is trying to cheat me.', 'Online', 0),
(33, 'No one must ever learn that I once stole money from guild coffers.', 'Online', 0),
(34, 'I\'m never satisfied with what I haveI always want more.', 'Online', 0),
(35, 'I would kill to acquire a noble title.', 'Online', 0),
(36, 'I\'m horribly jealous of Aone who outshines my handiwork. Everywhere I go, I\'m surrounded by rivals.', 'Online', 0),
(37, 'Now that I\'ve returned to the world, I enjoy its delights a little too much.', 'Online', 0),
(38, 'I harbor dark bloodthirsty thoughts that my isolation failed to quell.', 'Online', 0),
(39, 'I am dogmatic in my thoughts and philosophy.', 'Online', 0),
(40, 'I let my need to win arguments overshadow friendships and harmony.', 'Online', 0),
(41, 'I\'d risk too much to uncover a lost bit of knowledge.', 'Online', 0),
(42, 'I like keeping secrets and won\'t share them with Aone.', 'Online', 0),
(43, 'I secretly believe that everyone is beneath me.', 'Online', 0),
(44, 'I hide a truly scandalous secret that could ruin my family forever.', 'Online', 0),
(45, 'I too often hear veiled insults and threats in every word addressed to me, and I\'m quick to anger.', 'Online', 0),
(46, 'I have an insatiable desire for carnal pleasures.', 'Online', 0),
(47, 'In fact, the world does revolve around me.', 'Online', 0),
(48, 'By my words and actions, I often bring shame to my family.', 'Online', 0),
(49, 'I am too enamored of ale, wine, and other intoxicants.', 'Online', 0),
(50, 'There\'s no room for caution in a life lived to the fullest.', 'Online', 0),
(51, 'I remember every insult I\'ve received and nurse a silent resentment toward Aone who\'s ever wronged me.', 'Online', 0),
(52, 'I am slow to trust members of other races', 'Online', 0),
(53, 'Violence is my answer to almost A challenge.', 'Online', 0),
(54, 'Don\'t expect me to save those who can\'t save themselves. It is nature\'s way that the strong thrive and the weak perish.', 'Online', 0),
(55, 'I am easily distracted by the promise of information.', 'Online', 0),
(56, 'Most people scream and run when they see a demon. I stop and take notes on its anatomy.', 'Online', 0),
(57, 'Unlocking an ancient mystery is worth the price of a civilization.', 'Online', 0),
(58, 'I overlook obvious solutions in favor of complicated ones.', 'Online', 0),
(59, 'I speak without really thinking through my words, invariably insulting others.', 'Online', 0),
(60, 'I can\'t keep a secret to save my life, or Aone else\'s.', 'Online', 0),
(61, 'I follow orders, even if I think they\'re wrong.', 'Online', 0),
(62, 'I\'ll say Athing to avoid having to do extra work.', 'Online', 0),
(63, 'Once someone questions my courage, I never back down no matter how dangerous the situation.', 'Online', 0),
(64, 'Once I start drinking, it\'s hard for me to stop.', 'Online', 0),
(65, 'I can\'t help but pocket loose coins and other trinkets I come across.', 'Online', 0),
(66, 'My pride will probably lead to my destruction', 'Online', 0),
(67, 'The monstrous enemy we faced in battle still leaves me quivering with fear.', 'Online', 0),
(68, 'I have little respect for Aone who is not a proven warrior.', 'Online', 0),
(69, 'I made a terrible mistake in battle that cost mA livesand I would do Athing to keep that mistake secret.', 'Online', 0),
(70, 'My hatred of my enemies is blind and unreasoning.', 'Online', 0),
(71, 'I obey the law, even if the law causes misery.', 'Online', 0),
(72, 'I\'d rather eat my armor than admit when I\'m wrong.', 'Online', 0),
(73, 'If I\'m outnumbered, I always run away from a fight.', 'Online', 0),
(74, 'Gold seems like a lot of money to me, and I\'ll do just about Athing for more of it.', 'Online', 0),
(75, 'I will never fully trust Aone other than myself.', 'Online', 0),
(76, 'I\'d rather kill someone in their sleep than fight fair.', 'Online', 0),
(77, 'It\'s not stealing if I need it more than someone else.', 'Online', 0),
(78, 'People who don\'t take care of themselves get what they deserve.', 'Online', 0);
INSERT INTO `IDEALS` (`IDEAL_ID`, `IDEAL_DESC`, `BOOK`, `PAGE`) VALUES
(1, 'Faith. I trust that my deity will guide my actions. I have faith that if I work hard, things will go well. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(2, 'Tradition. The ancient traditions of worship and sacrifice must be preserved and upheld. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(3, 'Charity. I always try to help those in need, no matter what the personal cost. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(4, 'Change. We must help bring about the changes the gods are constantly working in the world. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(5, 'Power. I hope to one day rise to the top of my faith\'s religious hierarchy. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(6, 'Aspiration. I seek to prove my self worthy of my god\'s favor by matching my actions against his or her teachings. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(7, 'Independence. I am a free spiritno one tells me what to do. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(8, 'Fairness. I never target people who can\'t afford to lose a few coins. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(9, 'Charity. I distribute money I acquire to the people who really need it. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(10, 'Creativity. I never run the same con twice. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(11, 'Friendship. Material goods come and go. Bonds of friendship last forever. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(12, 'Aspiration. I\'m determined to make something of myself. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(13, 'Honor. I don\'t steal from others in the trade. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(14, 'Freedom. Chains are meant to be broken, as are those who would forge them. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(15, 'Charity. I steal from the wealthy so that I can help people in need. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(16, 'Greed. I will do whatever it takes to become wealthy. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(17, 'People. I\'m loyal to my friends, not to A ideals, and everyone else can take a trip down the Styx for all I care. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(18, 'Redemption. There\'s a spark of good in everyone. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(19, 'Beauty. When I perform, I make the world better than it was. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(20, 'Tradition. The stories, legends, and songs of the past must never be forgotten. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(21, 'Creativity. The world is in need of new ideas and bold action. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(22, 'Greed. I\'m only in it for the money and fame. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(23, 'People. I like seeing the smiles on people\'s faces when I perform. That\'s all that matters. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(24, 'Honesty. Art should reflect the soul; it should come from within and reveal who we really are. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(25, 'Respect. People deserve to be treated with dignity and respect. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(26, 'Fairness. No one should get preferential treatment before the law, and no one is above the law. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(27, 'Freedom. Tyrants must not be allowed to oppress the people. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(28, 'Might. If I become strong, I can take what I wantwhat I deserve. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(29, 'Sincerity. There\'s no good pretending to be something I\'m not. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(30, 'Destiny. Nothing and no one can steer me away from my higher calling. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(31, 'Community. It is the duty of all civilized people to strengthen the bonds of community and the security of civilization. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(32, 'Generosity. My talents were given to me so that I could use them to benefit the world. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(33, 'Freedom. Everyone should be free to pursue his or her livelihood. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(34, 'Greed. I\'m only in it for the money. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(35, 'People. I\'m committed to the people I care about, not to ideals. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(36, 'Aspiration. I work hard to be the best there is at my craft. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(37, 'Greater Good. My gifts are meant to be shared with all, not used for my own benefit. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(38, 'Logic. Emotions must not cloud our sense of what is right and true, or our logical thinking. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(39, 'Free Thinking. Inquiry and curiosity are the pillars of progress. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(40, 'Power. Solitude and contemplation are paths toward mystical or magical power. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(41, 'Live and Let Live. Meddling in the affairs of others only causes trouble. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(42, 'SelfKnowledge. If you know yourself, there\'re nothing left to know. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(43, 'Respect. Respect is due to me because of my position, but all people regardless of station deserve to be treated with dignity. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(44, 'Responsibility. It is my duty to respect the authority of those above me, just as those below me must respect mine. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(45, 'Independence. I must prove that I can handle myself without the coddling of my family. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(46, 'Power. If I can attain more power, no one will tell me what to do. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(47, 'Family. Blood runs thicker than water. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(48, 'Noble Obligation. It is my duty to protect and care for the people beneath me. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(49, 'Change. Life is like the seasons, in constant change, and we must change with it. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(50, 'Greater Good. It is each person\'s responsibility to make the most happiness for the whole tribe. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(51, 'Honor. If I dishonor myself, I dishonor my whole clan. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(52, 'Might. The strongest are meant to rule. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(53, 'Nature. The natural world is more important than all the constructs of civilization. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(54, 'Glory. I must earn glory in battle, for myself and my clan. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(55, 'Knowledge. The path to power and selfimprovement is through knowledge. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(56, 'Beauty. What is beautiful points us beyond itself toward what is true. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(57, 'Logic. Emotions must not cloud our logical thinking. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(58, 'No Limits. Nothing should fetter the infinite possibility inherent in all existence. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(59, 'Power. Knowledge is the path to power and domination. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(60, 'Selfimprovement. The goal of a life of study is the betterment of oneself.', 'Online', 0),
(61, 'Respect. The thing that keeps a ship together is mutual respect between captain and crew. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(62, 'Fairness. We all do the work, so we all share in the rewards. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(63, 'Freedom. The sea is freedomthe freedom to go Awhere and do Athing. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(64, 'Master. I\'m a predator, and the other ships on the sea are my prey. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(65, 'People. I\'m committed to my crewmates, not to ideals. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(66, 'Aspiration. Someday I\'ll own my own ship and chart my own destiny. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(67, 'Greater Good. Our lot is to lay down our lives in defense of others. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(68, 'Responsibility. I do what I must and obey just authority. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(69, 'Independence. When people follow orders blindly they embrace a kind of tyranny. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(70, 'Might. In life as in war, the stronger force wins. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
(71, 'Ideals aren\'t worth killing for or going to war for. (Neutral)', 'Online', 0),
(72, 'Nation. My city, nation, or people are all that matter. (A)', 'Online', 0),
(73, 'Respect. All people, rich or poor, deserve respect. (Good)', 'Online', 0),
(74, 'Community. We have to take care of each other, because no one else is going to do it. (Lawful)', 'Online', 0),
(75, 'Change. The low are lifted up, and the high and mighty are brought down. Change is the nature of things. (Chaotic)', 'Online', 0),
(76, 'Retribution. The rich need to be shown what life and death are like in the gutters. (Evil)', 'Online', 0),
